reviews.name: Brittany  B.
reviews.review:
ATTENTION: THIS PARKING GARAGE IS A SCAM!!! Do not go to this parking garage. It was right across from Pier 29 with "Public Parking" signs pointing to it. When I go to Pier 39, I usually park a few piers away to save money. I double and triple checked the sign to make sure there really was a "10 dollar flat rate" before four hours like we initially saw when we pulled into the garage. We saw nothing about having to get the ticket validated. Nothing other than the "10 dollar flat rate" that it claimed to have.

We make sure we get what we want to get done within four hours and make it back in time and lo and behold, we get charged 25 dollars! And then the scam artist of an employee said "Well there's a catch, you have to get it validated at the exploratorium for a 10 dollar flat rate." And he says otherwise it's 3 dollars every 30 minutes and then it caps out at 25 dollars. And considering we were back before four hours, that would be 24 dollars at the most if you do the math.

If you're going to charge something other than a flat rate, post that on the sign. And don't retrospectively make up a "3 dollars per every 30 minute rate" when, since I was only there for four hours, does not mathematically make sense. THIS PARKING LOT IS NOTHING BUT A SCAM. Park elsewhere unless you feel like getting robbed even more than you already do in San Francisco. L

reviews.name: Ashley D.
reviews.review: This parking lot is a rip off. The worker is extremely disrespectful. Their sign clearly says $15 flat rate, yet I was charged $25. Their pay machine has instructions with steps 1-3. However, it's incorrect. 1st step says insert payment. I paid with card. Next step is choose your time. As soon as I inserted my card the machine read $20 until a certain time, but I only needed one hour. I was looking for where to adjust the time then suddenly it said "completing transaction". I quickly pushed "cancel", but next thing that shows up is "printing receipt". I explained to the worker what happened and he said it was my fault because I was with two other people and we were causing a shadow that blocked the machine. Which is complete bullsh*t. The machine is right next to the lighted office and there's plenty of street lights. I read the instructions perfectly fine. I have the picture to prove the instructions are not clear. He showed us that we were suppose to insert payment then click the small yellow button located on the bottom right. How is anyone suppose to know to click that when it's not stated anywhere on the machine? Plus the yellow button said for oversized vehicles. My car is not oversized. For step 1, there is a picture of three buttons that says $5, $15, $20. So we clicked $5 thinking it would just be $5, but instead it added $5 to the $20. When we asked the worker if anything could be done, so we wouldn't be charged $25 all he said was "you guys are good" as in we're ok

reviews.review: Myself and three others just left an event at the Masonic. The event staff inside the venue were fantastic, however the parking staff in the Masonic parking lot treated us terribly. Upon entry to our event (VIP dashboard confessional and third eye blind event) there was a sign posted saying event parking was $30.  We also received an email from live nation stating the parking was $30. When we paid we were charged $38. The parking attendant called the lot manager, who was EXTREMELY rude to us. He was rude, and talked down to us like a bully and said there was no sign because the event didn't start until 4, when in fact the VIP event started much earlier. He told us too bad, and that he's the manager and no one is going to give us our money back. We asked him if he put up the sign himself and he said no. He said "well did you take a picture of the sign? Do you have proof?" He was really mean to us, all over a measly $8. We are more upset over how degrading his speech was than the money itself. We are surely never parking in this parking garage again. He also refused to give our parking ticket back, and when we tried to leave he wouldn't let us out and made us back up and go around just to be rude. We felt like he basically told us to f-off. (Sorry about the language)

The 490 Post Street Garage valet proceeded quickly to retrieve my car and help me to the safety of my locked car. The "street person commented, "What a nice ride." By this time approximately 5 minutes, the street person exited, and the valet ran out of the driveway to usher me out to safety. I am so sad about the state of affairs in our downtown area of San Francisco. I am a 5th generation native and thank you for helping me last night.

He said that I passed my "grace period" after my payment. This does not make ANY sense. A person can stay 1 hour plus 15 minutes for a grace period for $10. However, I stayed 52 minutes and needed to pay twice just because I followed the signs and paid before entering my car instead of paying by the gate. Literally the worst people. I literally fucking live there.

reviews.name: Sherri S.
reviews.review: ***DOG OWNERS BEWARE*** I began parking here on 9/3/2019 and on 9/16/2019-- after dropping my dog off at doggie day care-- I was told by the attendant that I was no longer able to park there because my car still smelled like my dog. It's a garage. A. Garage. full of mold, exhaust, and dust. I found parking down the street for the same price with less ridiculous valets. Also, their elevator was broken the entire time I parked there.

reviews.name: Frank T.
reviews.review: Best parking lot in SoMa hands down.

reviews.name: Michael R.
reviews.review: I was charged a full day day price for 2.5hrs.  I implore you to find s more honest parking vendor. There are plenty in the  vicinity.

reviews.name: Karlie I.
reviews.review: Stupid idiots. Decided to pain a wall in their garage but not post any signs so as I was waiting for my car I made the critical mistake of leaning on the wall. $300 skirt covered in yellow and black paint and ruined. My son’s jeans and sweater - covered and ruined. Dumb fools.

reviews.name: Vlad I.
reviews.review: Left my car in morning with everything perfect condition, got my car back as i was walking to my car valet person quickly run off.  Oh my windows is not all the way down, so i tried rolling up and realized it was off track. Now i'm going to spend my night figuring out how did it get fucked up. I know what are the chance for 40k bmw window to come off rails for first time ever?! Be warned.

reviews.name: Shrooz G.
reviews.review:
I've been parking here for a couple of months now. It's a valet service, not self park. The drivers are all very courteous. If you call them 15-20 minutes before you're ready to leave they will pull your car out so you don't have to wait. A big help during rush hour. 

They just raised their Early Bird Special (9:30am - 7:30pm) to $20.

reviews.name: Tabbi F.
reviews.review: This parking facility is deceptive. On Mission Street, the sign stated that parking is $18.00 before 9 am. When we drove into the lot, it cost us $40.00 even though it was before 9 am. When I explained to the attendant that the sign on Mission Street said it was $18, he was rude and basically said its if you don't want to park here for $40, them turn around and leave. He was completely rude and had manners to us.
